OL,6,FHis successor, Sir Tony Blair, then
OL,7,Fconsidered a voluntary ID card, but it
OL,8,Fwas not fully rolled out amid
OL,9,Fobjections from the Liberal Democrats
OL,10,Fand Conservatives. He has since called
OL,11,Ffor their introduction.
OL,13,FHis calls were backed up by Labour
OL,14,Fcampaign group Labour Together earlier
OL,15,Fthis year, which has been closely
OL,16,Flinked to Sir Keir and the Government.
OL,18,FThe think tank published a 30-page
OL,19,Fdocument in June in favour of the
OL,20,Fcards.
